pageContext.claim: “You [European Union] are not accepting our product. They are not accepting our farm product. I want to help the farmers and they don't accept it. And I said open up your countries.”
pageContext.analysis: The E.U. is the fourth-largest agricultural export market for the U.S., with exports of $11.6 billion in agricultural items to the European Union in 2016, a 55 percent increase from the year before.
